---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Zero" description="A little about me">
  <div class="terminal-container rounded-lg border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="terminal-header bg-gray-800 px-4 py-2 flex justify-between items-center">
      <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">zerodumb@ethics-journal:~/services$</span>
      <div class="flex space-x-2">
        <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500"></span>
        <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-yellow-500"></span>
        <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none p-6">
      <h1 class="text-terminal-green">About Zero</h1>
        <p>I didn’t go to MIT. I don’t work at Google. I build things, break things, and write about it when the dust settles.</p>

        <p>ZeroDumb started as a blog to document weird AI behavior, questionable client requests, and the growing need for ethical lines in tool-assisted dev work.</p>

        <p>I like matrix rain, static terminals, and hearing from non-weird humans. If you’re one of those: <a href="mailto:zero@zerodumb.dev">email me</a>.</p>

        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/ZeroDumb">GitHub</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://x.com/zerodumb_dev"> X</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://buymeacoffee.com/iamnotaskid">Buy Me Caffeine</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>Build carefully. Break responsibly.<br>
          Ask questions first. Hack later. Stay curious. Stay loud.
        </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

